					   <td>

			
			
			


<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
<tr>
	<td width="1%">&nbsp;</td>
	<td width="98%">

		<table width="100%">
		<tr>
			<td>
				<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="3"><b>    Shadow Knight Guide</b></font>
					<br>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">
					<b><A href="mailto:Delidgamond@hotmail.com">Vievictus</a> | 
		            11/16/1999 4:44:48 PM</b></font></p>
		         <a href="guides.asp">
		         <font face="verdana" size="2">Return to guide listing.</font></a>
					
					<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">Out of all the classes I've played as, and that's most of them, I've enjoyed the Shadow Kinght the best.  They are the most hateful class out there and are therefore the best.  Shadow Knight's Harm Touch ability is great to have only as a lifesaver and in drastic measures.  Just don't go wasting it away to gain your health back cause you don't want to wait. The Shadow Knight spells aren't that great for their lvl but if you think about it, it's a warrior that can suck life.  They also get pets which EQ have boosted their levels on them so they at least con blue to you when you first get them, at least that's what I heard.  Now that they have been given the life drain abilities, soloing is much easier than it was before.  I've tried all the races with the Shadoew Kninght and I like the Ogre the best.  Granted he doesn't get the healing rate of a troll but he get's more HP than a troll.  The Ogre Shadow Knight is ALMOST identenical to the ogre warrior, notice the ALMOST for you critics, so they can hit about as hard and get the same amount of life, plus, as a bonus, they get spells and a pet to do that little extra damage in their.  Kind of like when you start with the low level slam ability when your an ogre/troll.  I think the Shadow Knight should be more of a warrior type of class because their spells aren't that strong.  I've only gotten an Shadow Knight up to level 15 though so I don't know if the later spells are useful or not.  But all and all, I think the Shadow Knight is the best class to be.
			<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></p>
					</p>
			</td>
				<td>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td></tr>
