				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				  First of all i would like to say that each of you have a uniqe,respectable,point of view on the Sk.Afterall thats what separates us from one another and the rest of Norrath. We stand alone thats for sure.In group ventures,sometimes it seems we are still alone.I think its cause we each have a very different style,and strategy, than that of any other player,or charecter,in Norrath.The Sk is not,in my opinion,an &quot;in your face&quot; fighter.Instead the Sk must be sly and cautious at all times.Its how we survive.I'm sure you all agree when i say,if we jump into battle feet first,those feet will soon be running us back to our corpse quicker than we can shout help. Thats why unlike any other class,we must use our heads before going into battle.Yes we survive by watching our own asses and not anybody elses,even when we are grouped.We are the &quot;ninja&quot; of fighters and warriors if you will.The Sk,is by far the most difficult class to operate.Again thats my opinion.I must say the EVERQUEST staff have done an outstanding job at equalizing this class.If your struggling too hard with the Sk,its probably because your operating it like you would a barbarian or something.Try sneeking around the land,attacking from behind,and avoid going head on,or toe to toe with anybody.You'll lose that way.The Sk class is not for everybody.Its belongs to the most patient of players with a strategic way of thinking.Not your typical hack n slay class.Couple tips;group with players 1-2lvls lower than u so you gain exp.quicker.Dont send your pet in first.Its not there to protect you,its there to assist you,and it can do no good dead.Let it follow you instead,taunt creatures away from it.That will save mana,time,hp,and exp. in the long run.at lvl 9 when we first get our spells we expect them to perform like we are 9th lvl casters,wrong.WE have only begun.Group with others and use the spells to pull creatures to you,then run back behind the group and let the tanks do the manual labor.Cast a couple more times then draw your sword.Works for me.I'm lvl 12 and casting with a very high success rate.I love the Sk cause no 2 are the same.Not in the least.Enjoy fellow knights and stay in the shadows.
