				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I agree with the above comments, this is not really a guide just some opinions. I'm a level 15 SK and yes it is a struggle. But as a starting SK all you want to do is Kill Kill Kill, You want a guide. Here it is! Don't even think of qesting for a long time stay in FP until about lvl 20 (an then with a group) then go venture out. In the meantime, learn how to use your skills in battle, get all your skills as high as you can (1hs, 2hs, Bind Wound, Dodge, and all the casting skills) I suggest you kill lots of ORCS for good exp and faction.. you will also learn alot about the types of situations you can survive in when fighting ORCS! (HARM TOUCH... the great equalizer!!!) But you say DaC how do I make money to buy cool stuff?? At lvl 9 you get your Sense Unded spell. Use it to hunt down all the Skeletons in EC sell the bone chip stacks (the stacks sell for about 3pp ea but the big fish might pay 5pp ea for them). With this spell its almost unfair that SKs can do this better than anyone else.  Then move on to the Orcs after you have bought something to cover your Darkass. You must have patience the power and glory comes!! Your skills are what will save you and probably your group one day. Perfect them now before you get caught up in the questing and group thing. Even though I think a group of Shadow Knights is probably the nastiest combo there is. The true nature of the Shadow Knight is to solo. Because we are just that bad!!! I ususally never see anyone turning down SKs to join their groups, because they know how much damage we can do!<BR>
